    "However, the analysis of its abstract also revealed that it would not be relevant given the goals and scope of this literature review.The second stage consisted of identifying relevant studies based on the preceding findings and selecting the studies that were relevant to the subject.",
    "Although the relevance of ethics metrics and principles varies according to the domain (e.g., healthcare, law, education), we approach this work from a domain-agnostic perspective, as the implementation of each metric is the same regardless of the domain.",
